        <p>This page lists the file formats which are recommended when depositing in CLARIN-IS repository.</p>
        <h3>File Formats for Digital Preservation Policy</h3>
        <p>To ensure access and usability of your data to the broadest audience into the long term, the CLARIN-IS team has considered severl factors to to determine which file formats are recommended in CLARIN-IS infrastructure: </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Suitability for the type of resource and/or type of processing.</li>
            <li>Suitability for research by the designated communities.</li>
            <li>How widespread the format is: broadly used formats, not deprecated, known to the designated communities.</li>
            <li>Use of open source rather than proprietary format.</li>
        </ul>
    </info>
